    "en": {
      "title": "The government hid the truth about the economic crisis",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Acting President Ranil Wickremesinghe said in an interview with CNN that the government hid the truth regarding the economic crisis in Sri Lanka.",
        "Acting President Ranil Wickramasinghe said that the former President Gotabaya Rajapaksa's government hid the fact that Sri Lanka is bankrupt and needs to go to the International Monetary Fund to get rid of it.",
        "Mr. Ranil Wickramasinghe mentioned that he knows that the Sri Lankan people are suffering.",
        "Mr. Ranil Wickramasinghe pointed out that Sri Lanka's economy has gone backwards and the economy should be built from the grassroots level again.",
        "Mr. Wickramasinghe said that 5-10 years is not necessary to build Sri Lanka's economy.",
        "Mr. Wickramasinghe mentioned that by the end of next year, it will be possible to stabilize the economy of Sri Lanka and specifically by the year 2024, it will be possible to build a growing economy in Sri Lanka.",
        "CNN News Service reported that Mr. Ranil Wickramasinghe stated in the interview that he had spoken to former President Gotabhaya Rajapaksa when he went to Maldives and then to Singapore, but at this time he did not know whether Mr. Rajapaksa was in Singapore or somewhere else."
      ],
